===Etymology===
Anglo-Norman ''werre'' from Old Northern French ''werre'', a variant of {{OF.}} ''[[guerre]]'', from Old Franconian ''[[werra]]'', ultimately from Indo-European ''*werza-'', meaning "[[mixture]]" or "[[confusion]]."

